body:
This PR adds explicit symbol visibiliy with a cmake-based auto-generated header `thrift_export.h` for C++. For shared library builds, the header defines a number of macros. Most importantly it defines `THRIFT_EXPORT` on MSVC builds to ` __declspec( dllimport )` or ` __declspec( dllexport )`. CMake automatically adds the required compile-time define by which the definition of `THRIFT_EXPORT` is adjusted to either ` __declspec( dllimport )` or ` __declspec( dllexport )`.

With this header in place, explicit symbol visibility can be specified with the following modification from:
```
// Without any external symbol visibility:
class SomeClass {
...
}
```
change to:
```
// With full external symbol visibility:
#include "thrift_export.h"
class THRIFT_EXPORT SomeClass {
...
}
```
Its also possible to define partial visibility:
```
// With partial external symbol visibility:
#include "thrift_export.h"
class SomeClass {
    THRIFT_EXPORT int SomeMethod();
}
```

This approach can be transparently combined with the current approach to use `set(CMAKE_WINDOWS_EXPORT_ALL_SYMBOLS ON)` in `build/cmake/DefinePlatformSpecifc.cmake`. Furthermore, the header defines the macros on Unix such that it can be used to hide symbols on Unix platforms (see https://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/Visibility for details).
